India Equity Movers: ECE, Godrej Consumer, Idea, Phoenix Mills

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-07-06T04:36:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/india-equity-movers-ece-godrej-consumer-idea-phoenix-mills.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 9:40 a.m. in Mumbai, unless otherwise
stated.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
gained 23.29, or 0.1 percent, to 18,767.85. The BSE 200 Index
rose 0.1 percent to 2,325.50.  ECE Industries Ltd. (ECE)   rose 1.4 percent to 127.8
rupees, headed for the highest close in more than four months.
The electrical equipment supplier said it will pay up to 145
rupees a share to buy back as much as 8.42 percent of its equity
capital. ECE made the announcement in an advertisement in the
Business Standard newspaper today.  Godrej Consumer Products Ltd. (GCPL)   added 3 percent to
451.15 rupees, set for the highest closing price since September
2010. The Indian consumer company and U.S.-based chocolate and
confectionery maker Hershey Co. have called off their joint
venture in India, the Economic Times reported without saying
where it got the information. Hershey will sell its 51 percent
stake to Godrej Consumer for an undisclosed amount, the report
said.  Idea Cellular Ltd. (IDEA)   increased 1.5 percent to 78.15
rupees, bound for the steepest gain since more than a week.
Indiaâ€™s Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal
halted the government from imposing a fine of 2.5 billion rupees
($56 million) on Idea Cellular for overlapping wireless permits
following a planned merger with Spice Communications Ltd.  Phoenix Mills Ltd. (PHNX)   gained 1.5 percent to 197
rupees, headed for the highest closing level since May 20. The
developer is planning to expand by setting up shopping malls in
major cities like Mumbai, Bangalore and Chennai by March 2012,
the Business Standard reported citing managing director Atul Ruia.  To contact the reporters on this story:
